    "body": "Hi @abhinav-nehra your example is working as designed; your code ends up with both instances of requestValidator mounted at the root point (`/`) applying to all requests. You need to prefix your `requestValidator` with the desired path to actually validate. Or better yet, based on what I suspect you are doing, just add the requestValidator as middleware on the POST routes themselves.\r\n\r\nSince you provided screenshots, it would take me a while to type out all the code to give you a complete example, but here is the general gist of what I'm suggesting you do:\r\n```js\r\nregisterUser.post(requestValidator({ ... }), (req, res, next) => {\r\n})\r\n```\r\n",
