    "body": "Hi @abhinav-nehra unless you change the way you mount your router to mount the router itself at the path, there is no way to do it otherwise. You're welcome to contribute a PR to implement the feature, through :)\r\n\r\nExample of alternative method:\r\n```js\r\n// your login.js file\r\nmodule.exports = loginUser;\r\nloginUser.use(requestValidator({ ... })\r\nloginUser.post('/', (req, res, next) => {\r\n})\r\n\r\n// then you mount the router at the actual path\r\napp.use('/login', require('./path/to/login.js')\r\n```\r\n",
